abstract: Managed by Q start-up has raised $25 million from new investors in latest round of financing, despite offering terms that many might find unfavorable; company has succeeded with business model unlike that of many peers, including decision to hire full- and part-time employees over contractors.
lead_paragraph: The investors GV, formerly Google Ventures, and Kapor Capital provided the financing for the office cleaning and management company.

headline.main: Managed by Q, an On-Demand Start-Up, Raises $25 Million
